cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with visual question answering, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method for learning multimodal feature representations, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a self-attention mechanism also suggests the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with video stories, which could be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia).
